(303, 'Tupac: Resurrection', 'Documentary,', 'Filmmaker Lauren Lazin examines the life and music of rapper Tupac Shakur, who was murdered in 1996.', '169', 2003, '2020-10-23T04:00Z', '2020-10-23T06:30Z', '150', 'MV001419240000', '33301', '2003-11-14', 'en', 'Using interviews, photographs and home movies, this documentary presents the life of rapper Tupac Shakur. His mother, Afeni, is a Black Panther who spends part of her pregnancy in jail. Growing up in a politicized atmosphere, Shakur attends a performing arts high school in Baltimore, where he begins rapping. Success comes early, as do a series of legal problems, with arrests and accusations of violence against women leading up to his meteoric rise to fame and still-unsolved 1996 murder.', '14929'),
